fields.name: Reaction Time
fields.description: The time taken by a participant to respond to a stimulus.

fields.name: Accuracy
fields.description: The correctness of a participant's responses.

fields.name: Memory Recall
fields.description: The ability to remember previously presented information.

fields.name: Heart Rate
fields.description: The number of heartbeats per minute.

fields.name: Skin Conductance
fields.description: A measure of the skin's ability to conduct electricity, which varies with its moisture level.

fields.name: Pupil Dilation
fields.description: The expansion of the pupil, often in response to cognitive and emotional stimuli.

fields.name: Eye Movements
fields.description: The tracking of eye positions and movements.

fields.name: Attention Span
fields.description: The duration of sustained attention a participant can maintain.

fields.name: Perceived Stress
fields.description: A self-reported measure of stress experienced by the participant.

fields.name: Mood
fields.description: A self-reported measure of the participant's emotional state.

fields.name: Reaction Time Variability
fields.description: The variability in reaction times across multiple trials.

fields.name: Response Bias
fields.description: The tendency to respond in a particular way regardless of the stimulus.

fields.name: Task Engagement
fields.description: The level of involvement and effort a participant puts into a task.

fields.name: Decision Making Time
fields.description: The time taken by a participant to make a decision.

fields.name: Motor Coordination
fields.description: The ability of a participant to coordinate their movements.

fields.name: Verbal Fluency
fields.description: The ability to produce words fluently in a given amount of time.

fields.name: Impulse Control
fields.description: The ability to control impulses and delay gratification.

fields.name: Social Interactions
fields.description: The frequency and quality of a participant's social interactions.

fields.name: Cognitive Load
fields.description: The amount of mental effort being used in the working memory.

fields.name: Sleep Quality
fields.description: A measure of how well a participant sleeps, often self-reported.

fields.name: Emotional Arousal
fields.description: The intensity of emotional responses.

fields.name: Facial Expressions
fields.description: The movements of facial muscles as an indicator of emotions.

fields.name: Voice Tone
fields.description: The pitch and tone of voice as an indicator of emotions.

fields.name: Error Rates
fields.description: The frequency of errors made by participants during a task.

fields.name: Learning Curve
fields.description: The rate of improvement in performing a task over time.

fields.name: Mental Fatigue
fields.description: A state of mental exhaustion affecting cognitive functions.

fields.name: Self-Efficacy
fields.description: The belief in one's ability to succeed in specific situations.

fields.name: Intrinsic Motivation
fields.description: The internal drive to perform an activity for its own sake.

fields.name: Extrinsic Motivation
fields.description: The drive to perform an activity for external rewards or pressures.

fields.name: Social Support
fields.description: The perception and reality of being cared for by others.

fields.name: Task Difficulty
fields.description: The level of challenge presented by a task.

fields.name: Confidence Level
fields.description: The degree of certainty a participant feels about their abilities.

fields.name: Behavioral Intent
fields.description: A participant's intention to perform a certain behavior.

fields.name: Attention to Detail
fields.description: The ability to notice and consider the finer points of a task.

fields.name: Stress Level
fields.description: The amount of stress a participant is experiencing.

fields.name: Conflict Resolution Skills
fields.description: The ability to effectively resolve conflicts.
